// $Id$

- What is this?
  mod_fd_transfer.c provides a module for websocket and parallel request handling using Linux's open file descriptor transfer
  It is a plugin to lighttpd HTTP server ver 1.4.30( http://www.lighttpd.net/ )

- How does mod_fd_transfer work?
  Please see the 2 documents for their architecture and internals.

  https://github.com/aalap-shah/lighttpd-mod_fd_transfer/blob/master/ModFDTransferInternals.doc
  https://github.com/aalap-shah/lighttpd-mod_fd_transfer/blob/master/LibStratusInternals.doc

- How can I use this?
  First, please do like this.

  $ git clone git://github.com/aalap-shah/lighttpd-mod_fd_transfer.git

  and follow the instructions in INSTALL.

  for QUICK START, plz read Wiki.

  https://github.com/aalap-shah/lighttpd-mod_fd_transfer/wiki

